NORTH CAROLINA A&T STATE UNIVERSITY
STEP2NLS WITH STEM CORE – SUCCESSFUL TRAINING AND EFFECTIVE PIPELINES TO NATIONAL LABORATORIES WITH STEM CORE
THE GOALS OF STEP2NLS INCLUDE:
•	STRENGTHENING THE MSI STEM CAPACITY AND RESEARCH EXPERIENCE IN BOTH ENGINEERING (TOPIC AREA #3) AND CYBERSECURITY (TOPIC AREA #2);
O	ENGAGING STUDENTS FROM HBCUS, HSIS, AND TCUS IN THE STEP2NLS PROJECT;
O	BUILDING A SUSTAINABLE STEP2NLS PIPELINE THAT WILL ENDURE WELL INTO THE FUTURE;
•	INCREASING NL-SCIENTIST-TO-MSI-SCIENTIST INTERACTIONS BY ENGAGING DIRECTLY AND THROUGH STUDENT INTERACTIONS;
•	GROWING THE NUMBER OF MINORITY STUDENTS WHO GRADUATE WITH STEM DEGREES; AND
•	GROWING THE NUMBER OF MINORITY GRADUATES THAT JOIN THE DOE/NNSA STEM WORKFORCE.

GENERAL OBJECTIVES:
IN SUPPORT OF THE GOALS, GENERAL OBJECTIVES FOR STEP2NLS ARE TO:
•	STRENGTHEN THE RESEARCH AND EDUCATION CAPABILITIES AT AN HBCU (NCA&T), HSI (NMSU), AND TCU (NAVAJO TECH) AND 5 ASSOCIATED COLLEGES CLOSE TO THESE MSIS (GUILFORD TECHNICAL CC, FORSYTH TECHNICAL CC, CENTRAL NEW MEXICO CC, DOÑA ANA CC, AND UNM-GALLUP);
•	BUILD CAPACITY OF UNDERSERVED STUDENTS TO EXCEL IN STEM BY PROVIDING EXPERIENTIAL TRAINING;
•	ENLARGE THE SCIENTIFIC AND TECHNICAL KNOWLEDGE IN ENGINEERING AND CYBERSECURITY; AND
•	INSURE THAT STEP2NLS IS SUSTAINABLE AND SCALABLE.
